        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer975945996" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11293571082904646783">This rating is only for the vampire Who Stole Christmas. The plot of this short had quite a bit of potential but overall ended up being rather lackluster as a whole. The heroine is almost too much of a good thing...too good it comes off as a little annoying rather than super sweet. The hero is a basket case. He has tons of issues and is super broody but not in a hot way so much as im a sociopath and will kill my enemies kind of thing. The romance was rushed and underdeveloped and the sex scenes </span>
  <span id="freeText11293571082904646783" style="display:none">This rating is only for the vampire Who Stole Christmas. The plot of this short had quite a bit of potential but overall ended up being rather lackluster as a whole. The heroine is almost too much of a good thing...too good it comes off as a little annoying rather than super sweet. The hero is a basket case. He has tons of issues and is super broody but not in a hot way so much as im a sociopath and will kill my enemies kind of thing. The romance was rushed and underdeveloped and the sex scenes left me..room temp. Nothing awful but also nothing worth mentioning. as i said the plot had the potential to be quite interesting but the world was underdeveloped. I could live without extra details on the vamp side of things despite differences in the species among different authors i at least have a base to work off of in my head. Daimons who are really more like angels? not so much. The writing wasnt terrible but again not really worth mentioning. it wasnt bad enough to be a dnf but defintiely not good enough to recommend/reread</span>
